iv><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig06a.jpeg" height="718" width="938" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig06a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig06b.jpeg" height="718" width="938" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig06b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig07.jpeg" height="719" width="937" aria-labelledby="fig07" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7</span> Cystic metastatic rectal cancer in a 74-year-old woman. Equilibrium phase CECT image shows the ragged inner surface (white arrowheads) of the mass and the irregular internal enhancing septa (black arrowhead).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig07">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig08.jpeg" height="719" width="938" aria-labelledby="fig08" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8</span> Cystic liver metastasis that originated from an ovarian granulosa cell tumor in a 62-year-old patient. Equilibrium phase CECT image depicts a multilocular cystic lesion with enhancement of the septa and solid portions (arrowhead) in the center.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig08">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig09.jpeg" height="690" width="900" aria-labelledby="fig09" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9</span> Metastatic GIST treated with imatinib mesylate in a 17-year-old woman. Equilibrium phase CECT image shows a cystic mass with internal septa of varied thicknesses and multiple mural nodules.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig09">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig10a.jpeg" height="663" width="938" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig10a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig10b.jpeg" height="665" width="938" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig10b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig10c.jpeg" height="665" width="937" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig10c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig11a.jpeg" height="728" width="951" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig11b.jpeg" height="728" width="924" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig11b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig12.jpeg" height="690" width="900" aria-labelledby="fig12" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12</span> Pyogenic liver abscess in a 44-year-old man. Axial postcontrast (120 seconds) CECT image delineates the double target sign, which consists of a hypoattenuating central area surrounded by an inner hyperattenuating ring (arrow) and an outer hypoattenuating zone (arrowheads), in the left hepatic lobe.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig12">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig13a.jpeg" height="719" width="938" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig13a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig13b.jpeg" height="719" width="937" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig13b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig13c.jpeg" height="719" width="938" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.335125063&amp;id=fig13c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.335125063/asset/images/large/125063fig14a.jpeg" height="719" width="938" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/act